Package: MotionR
Title: Analyze accelerometer data (x, y, z configuration)
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("William", "HangasjÃ¤rvi", , "william.hangasjarvi@ki.se", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: This package helps you handle classic accelerometer data with x-, y-, and z-coordinates. This by providing three functions that 1). Combines x-, y-, and z-coordinates into a single "acceleration vector"; 2). Smoothens raw data in set time windows; 3). Applies the smoothening to the entire data set. The package comes with a practice data set "accelerometer_data" which you can access by running load("data/accelerometer_data").
